topics.body:
"@twistedmetalero":/dis/the-time-wasting-thread/post/541ce5756368720737d90100#post_541ce5756368720737d90100
For the cpu fan for the love of god do not remove the gray paste like thing on the end of the copper plating.  Why?  That's the cpu headsink paste; if you remove it your computer's fucked.  On second thought don't fuck with that part; sure using the compressed air on the fan is fine, but maintaining your headsink paste is a pain in the ass.

If it's just the regular fan not attached to your motherboard it's fine to mess with that though.
